(3, 4, '1st step - CONNECT THE NETWORK DISCS \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'', 4, '2010-08-16 17:05:01', '<strong><u>1st step - CONNECT THE NETWORK DISCS &nbsp;\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\':</u></strong><br /><br /><u><strong>Setup the \'Q\' disk:</strong></u><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>Q</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Quasar</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup the \'S\' disk:</u></strong><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>S</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Stamp3</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup the \'T\' disk:</u></strong><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>T</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Test</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Checking:</u></strong><br />A window is automatically opened at the end of each setup. The new network disc data are displayed<br /><br /><u><strong>Remarks:</strong></u><br />Use only the \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as Qasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters to identify the network disks<br />', '', ''),
(4, 5, '2nd step - Install and Setup the ODBC Server', 4, '2010-08-16 17:30:40', '<p><strong><u>2nd step - Install and Setup the ODBC Server</u></strong></p><p><strong><u>INSTALL THE ODBC SERVER:</u></strong></p><p><strong><u>Setup:</u></strong><br />Use the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\Setup\\ODBC\\mysql-connector-odbc-5.1.6-win32.msi</font>\' program and run it<br /><br /><strong><u>Remarks:</u></strong><br />This setup program is a standard program. Use all standard answers<br /><br /><strong><u>SETUP THE ODBC SERVER:</u></strong><br />Setup:<br />Open the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Setting Panel</font>\'<br />In the Setting Panel, double click on the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Administration Tools</font>\' icon<br />In the Administration Tools Panel, double click on the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Data sources (ODBC)</font>\'<br />Select the tab \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">User data sources</font>\'<br /><br />Repeat <strong>5</strong> time <em>(for each base)</em><br />-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br />Click on the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Add&hellip;</font>\' button and select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">MySQL ODBC.X.X</font>\' protocol<br />Complete the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Login</font>\' tabs with this information:<br /><table border=\"1\" align=\"center\"><thead><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Base 1</strong></td><td>&nbsp;<strong>Base 2</strong></td><td><strong>Base 3&nbsp;</strong></td><td><strong>Base 4</strong>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Base 5&nbsp;</strong></td></tr></thead><caption>&nbsp;</caption><tbody><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Data source name</strong></td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3</td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3ate</td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3drv</td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3inst</td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3uut</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Description</strong></td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3</td><td>&nbsp;Ate database</td><td>&nbsp;Driver database</td><td>&nbsp;Instrument parameters</td><td>&nbsp;UUT database</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Server</strong></td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Port <em>(if need)</em></strong></td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;User</strong></td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Password</strong></td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Database <em>(select)</em></strong></td><td>&nbsp;stamp3</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3ate</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3drv</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3inst</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3uut</td></tr></tbody></table></p><p align=\"left\"><br /><strong><u>Checking:</u></strong><br />It&rsquo;s possible to use the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Test</font>\' button to check the access at the MySQL database</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ''),
