(6, 1, 'Wizard XML file format description', 4, '2010-08-16 15:01:21', '<p><strong><u>XML format for the Wizard Plug-in descriptor</u></strong><br />All the examples are issued from the SCPI parameter command into the HP 34970 instrument &sect;5<br />Note 1: the order of parameter have an importance to constitute easily the list of parameters<br />Note 2: to write the New Line command like  write: &nbsp;&rarr; &nbsp;\\<font color=\"#ff0000\">&lt;</font>NL\\<font color=\"#ff0000\">&gt;</font><br /><br /><strong><u>Global structure</u></strong></p><p><strong>wizard</strong></p><blockquote><font color=\"#800000\">header<br /></font></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#800000\">/header</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#333399\">instrument<br /></font></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#333399\">/instrument</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#ff0000\">functions</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#808000\">function name=&quot;&quot;</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#008000\">parameters</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#0000ff\">parameter label=&quot;&quot;<br /></font></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#0000ff\">/parameter</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#008000\">/parameters</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#808000\">/function</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#ff0000\">/functions</font><br /></blockquote><strong>/wizard</strong><br /><br /><strong><u>Header structure</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\"><strong>header</strong></font><br /><blockquote>program  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; alway </font><font color=\"#800080\">Stamp3</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>function  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; alway </font><font color=\"#800080\">Plug-in</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; example: HP 34970 A</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>module <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; use the name of the VI <em>(plug-in)</em> associated with this XML file</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>use  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; BASIC_PANEL if standard or the path of the specific panel.vi to be used</font>&nbsp;<br /></blockquote><font color=\"#800000\"><strong>/header</strong></font><br /><br /><strong><u>Instrument structure</u></strong> <br /><font color=\"#333399\"><strong>instrument</strong></font><br /><blockquote>supplier  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; name of the instrument supplier</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>reference  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; instrument reference like: HP34970A</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>who  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; who have created this XML parameters</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>when  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; When this XML document has created</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>revision  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Revision of this document</font> <br /></blockquote><font color=\"#333399\"><strong>/instrument</strong></font><br /><br /><strong><u>Functions structure</u></strong><br />List of instruments <font color=\"#808000\">function</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Include all the functions describe for the instrument</font><br /><br /><strong><u>Function structure</u></strong> <br /><font color=\"#808000\"><strong>function name=&quot;&quot;</strong></font>&nbsp;&rarr;  use an unique label to identify the instrument function like: MEASure:VOLTage:DC&nbsp;<br /><blockquote>label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like MEAS:VOLT:DC</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; global format to describe the SCPI command with one \'%s\' like: &quot;MEAS:VOLT:DC? %s&quot;</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>parameters  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; the entry of parameters list <em>(the parameters data replace dynamically the %s into the command format)</em></font> <br /></blockquote><font color=\"#808000\"><strong>/function</strong></font><br /><br /><strong><u>Parameters structure</u></strong><br />List of function <font color=\"#008000\">parameter</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Include all the parameter describe for the function</font><br /><br /><strong><u>Parameter structure</u></strong> <br /><font color=\"#008000\"><strong>parameter</strong></font><strong><font color=\"#008000\"> </font><font color=\"#008000\">label=&quot;&quot;</font></strong> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; use an unique label to identify the parameter into a function like: Auto</font><br /><blockquote>type  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; type for parameter. select: INT or REAL or BOOL or STRING or LIST or SWITCH or SW_EXT</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>need  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; if true the parameter is alway need. if false the operator can select to use or not the parameter</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><em>parameters</em> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; depending of type, see TYPE parameter description</font></blockquote><p><font color=\"#008000\"><strong>/parameter</strong></font><br /><br /><strong><u>TYPE parameter description</u></strong><br /><br /><strong>INT</strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_int.jpg\" alt=\"XML INT\" width=\"196\" height=\"82\" />&nbsp;</p><p>mini &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; minimal value accepted</font><br />maxi  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; maximal value accepted</font><br />default  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting</font><br />unit  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like V, mA, Hz, ...</font><br />format  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like %d, %03d,... used to convert the integer into a string</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;CLOS (@%s)&quot; used in global SCPI command ROUT:CLOS ()</font><br /><br /><strong>REAL</strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_real.jpg\" alt=\"XML REAL\" width=\"192\" height=\"82\" /></p><p>mini &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; minimal value accepted</font><br />maxi  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; maximal value accepted</font><br />default  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting</font><br />unit  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like V, mA, Hz</font><br />format  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like %f, %3.1f,... used to convert the real value into a string</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;GAIN %s&quot; used in global SCPI command SCAL:GAIN</font> <br /><br /><strong>BOOL</strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_bool.jpg\" alt=\"XML BOOL\" width=\"192\" height=\"80\" /></p><p>command &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;:AUTO %s&quot; used in global SCPI command RANGE:AUTO {OFF|ON}</font><br />label_true  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; true label displayed like: Auto = ON</font><br />command_true  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; string used for the true selection like: ON</font><br />label_false  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; false label displayed like: Auto = OFF</font><br />command_false <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; string used for the false selection like: OFF</font><br /><br /><strong>STRING</strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_string.jpg\" alt=\"XML STRING\" width=\"195\" height=\"80\" /></p><p>default &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;:TEXT \\&quot;%s\\&quot; used in global SCPI command DISPlay:TEXT</font> <br /><br /><strong>LIST</strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_list.jpg\" alt=\"XML LIST\" width=\"193\" height=\"81\" /></p><p>command &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;:BAND %s&quot; used in global SCPI command VOLTage:AC:BANDwidth {3|20|200|MIN|MAX}</font><br />default  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting like: 1 to select 20 (index start at 0)</font><br />item_Nbr  &rarr; number of item in the list<br />Items  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; container of items list</font><br />Item_01  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label &amp; command used for the 1st item</font><br />Item_02  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label &amp; command used for the 2nd item</font><br />... ... ...<br />Item_nn  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label &amp; command used for the last item</font><br /><br /><strong>SWITCH</strong> and <strong>SW_EX</strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_switch.jpg\" alt=\"XML SWITCH\" width=\"194\" height=\"79\" /></p><p>state0label &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label on middle position like: O</font><br />state0value  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; value on middle position like: O</font><br />state1label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label on low position like: L</font><br />state1value  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; value on low position like: L</font><br />state2label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label on high position like: H</font><br />state2value  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; value on high position like: H</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;SQ%s&quot; used as command line for the QuadCheck 7564A SQLHHOOOOO</font></p>', '', ''),
