ont></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"> <br /><font color=\"#808000\"><strong>function name=&quot;&quot;</strong></font></font><font color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;&rarr;  use an unique label to identify the instrument function like: MEASure:VOLTage:DC&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#ff0000\"><br /><blockquote>label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like MEAS:VOLT:DC</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; global format to describe the SCPI command with one \'%s\' like: &quot;MEAS:VOLT:DC? %s&quot;</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>parameters  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; the entry of parameters list <em>(the parameters data replace dynamically the %s into the command format)</em></font> <br /></blockquote><font color=\"#808000\"><strong>/function</strong></font><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Parameters structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><br /></font><font color=\"#000000\">List of function</font><font color=\"#ff0000\"> <font color=\"#008000\">parameter</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Include all the parameter describe for the function</font><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Parameter structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"> <br /><font color=\"#008000\"><strong>parameter</strong></font><strong><font color=\"#008000\"> </font><font color=\"#008000\">label=&quot;&quot;</font></strong> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; use an unique label to identify the parameter into a function like: Auto</font><br /><blockquote>type  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; type for parameter. select: INT or REAL or BOOL or STRING or LIST or SWITCH or SW_EXT</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>need  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; if true the parameter is alway need. if false the operator can select to use or not the parameter</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><em>parameters</em> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; depending of type, see TYPE parameter description</font></blockquote><p>