th: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">File label</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Path of the file that contains the list of the parameters to read, and the expected values</font><br /></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><p><strong><u>5. File infos</u></strong></p><blockquote><p>&nbsp;With the ASCII plugin, it\'s possible to read, send or check a list of values given in a file (whose path is given in the <font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></font> parameter).</p><p>The following example gives an overview of the informations that can be found in this kind of file : </p><p><font color=\"#999999\">[UUT_DESCRIPTION]<br />serial =UUT_SERIAL</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">reference = UUT_REF<br />date = MM/DD/YYYY<br />time = HH:MM:SS</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">path_template = path/to/the/template.ini</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\"><br />[PARAMETERS]<br />post_delay = 0.5<br /><br />[SETTINGS]<br />SET_U_UTIL = 230.0<br />SET_U_BATT = 100.0<br />etc.</font></p><p>The first section (<font color=\"#999999\">UUT_DESCRIPTION</font>) gives the global informations relative to the unit under test.</p><p>The second section (<font color=\"#999999\">PARAMETERS</font>) sets the plugin parameter.The &quot;<font color=\"#999999\">post_delay</font>&quot; parameter sets the wait time (in seconds) when reading or sending parameters. It must be adapted to the unit under test time response (default value : 0.5 second. </p><p>The last section (<font color=\"#999999\">SETTINGS</font>) lists all the parameters that will be read, sent or check in the unit under test.</p></blockquote>', '', ''),
(78, 6, 'SCPI commands for the ASCII plug-in (Stamp3PlugInASCII.vi)', 5, '2010-08-25 13:16:00', '<p><strong><u>SCPI commands for the ASCII plug-in (Stamp3PlugInASCII.vi</u></strong>)</p><br /><p>&nbsp;<u><strong>1. Plug-in setting : </strong></u></p><blockquote><p>This section gives all the SCPI commands necessary to the serial port configuration. </p></blockquote><blockquote><p><em><u>1.1. Initialization :</u></em></p><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">COMx:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">9600,8</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"174\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"height: 24px; width: 80px\">&nbsp;Explanation : </td><td style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#800000\">COMx</font></td><td style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Serial port </font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">9600</font>&nbsp; <br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Baud rate (bits/s)</font> </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">8</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Data bits</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Parity (0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;odd&quot;, 2 : &quot;even&quot;, 3 : &quot;mark&quot;, 4 : &quot;space&quot;)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\"