(85, 11, 'Generic variables list and usage', 4, '2010-08-27 10:53:24', '<p><font size=\"4\"><strong><u>Generic variables available</u></strong></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>This generic variables can be used into the test specification to facilitate the description</p><p><strong>Note:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>To use this generic variables in place of value, write the label into two \'<strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><font size=\"3\">~</font></font></strong>\' char like this : <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><font size=\"3\">~</font></font></strong><strong><font color=\"#3366ff\">SCAN_SERIAL SKU</font></strong><strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><font size=\"3\">~</font></font></strong>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Examples:</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><blockquote><u>Display an GUI pop-up with the bitmap name automatically set in accordance with the UUT</u>&nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote><font size=\"2\">DIV:USER:GUI:VALID(Product &rsquo;<strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">~SCAN_REF~</font></strong>&rsquo; connexion,Raccordement du produit &rsquo;<strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">~SCAN_REF~</font></strong>&rsquo;,Title xx,S:\\Network Power Solution\\Bitmaps\\UnitHypotFunctionalTest\\Connexion\\<font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>~SCAN_REF~</strong></font>.jpg)&nbsp;</font></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><blockquote><u>Set automatically the Hipot QuadCheck instrument with the setting need for the UUT</u> &nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote>MEAS:(FF&lt;NL&gt;FS&lt;NL&gt;SY <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">~GND_AMPS~</font></strong>&lt;NL&gt;S0 <strong><font color=\"#ff0000\">~GND_OHMS~</font></strong>&lt;NL&gt;S1 0&lt;NL&gt;S2 <font color=\"#ff0000\"><strong>~GND_TIME~</strong></font>&lt;NL&gt;S3 4&lt;NL&gt;S4 25.0&lt;NL&gt;FA&lt;NL&gt;) ~(%)~</blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Variables list:</strong></p><p><font color=\"#3366ff\">SCAN_REF	SKU</font> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Reference</font><br /><font color=\"#3366ff\">SCAN_SERIAL SKU</font> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Serial number<