t color=\"#808080\">→</font></td><td class=\"mceVisualAid\"><font color=\"#808080\">Path of the file in which the data read will be stored</font><font color=\"#808080\"> (**)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><p><font color=\"#808080\">(**) : See Paragraph 5 for more details</font>&nbsp; </p></blockquote><p><b><u>4. Check data</u></b></p><blockquote>This section gives all the available SCPI commands to check data content from the unit under test via the serial port.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br></blockquote><blockquote><i><font color=\"#999999\">Note : For each data type (order, parameter, string, file), the \"</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#999999\">\"   parameter refers to the definition of the data, made in the STAMP   settings (the label being linked to the product address where the data   will be written). </font></i></blockquote><blockquote><i><u>4.1. Status :</u></i></blockquote><blockquote> <blockquote><table class=\"mceVisualAid\" border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mceVisualAid\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px;\" align=\"left\">Command :</td><td class=\"mceVisualAid\"><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:WSTATUS(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,STATE,TIME,LOOP</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">) </font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table class=\"mceVisualAid\" border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mceVisualAid\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px;\" valign=\"top\">Explanation : <br></td><td class=\"mceVisualAid\" style=\"width: 40px;\" valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td class=\"mceVisualAid\" style=\"width: 20px;\" valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">→</font> <br></td><td class=\"mceVisualAid\" style=\"width: