quote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:WSTRING</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">,STRING,TIME,LOOP</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">) </font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">String label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">STRING</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Expected string value<br /></font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">TIME</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum time before end of check</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LOOP</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum number of check attempts</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"> <font color=\"#008080\">VAR</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Variable in which the string will be stored </font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>4.4. File :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:CFILE</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,PATH</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">File label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Path of the file that contains the list of the parameters to read, and the expected values</font><br /></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><p><strong><u>5. File infos</u></strong></p><blockquote><p>&nbsp;With the ASCII plugin, it\'s possible to read, send or check a list of values given in a file (whose path is given in the <font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></font> parameter).</p><p>The following example gives an overview of the informations that can be found in this kind of file : </p><p><font color=\"#999999\">[UUT_DESCRIPTION]<br />serial =UUT_SERIAL</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">reference = UUT_REF<br />date = MM/DD/YYYY<br />time = HH:MM:SS</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">path_template = path/to/the/template.ini</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\"><br />[PARAMETERS]<br />post_delay = 0.5<br /><br />[SETTINGS]<br />SET_U_UTIL = 230.0<br />SET_U_BATT = 100.0<br />etc.</font></p><p>The first section (<font color=\"#999999\">UUT_DESCRIPTION</font>) gives the global informations relative to the unit under test.</p><p>The second section (<font color=\"#999999\">PARAMETERS</font>) sets the plugin parameter.The &quot;<font color=\"#999999\">post_delay</font>&quot;   parameter sets the wait time (in seconds) when reading or sending   parameters. It must be adapted to the unit under test time response   (default value : 0.5 second). </p><p>The last section (<font color=\"#999999\">SETTINGS</font>) lists all the parameters that will be read, sent or check in the unit under test.</p></blockquote>', '', ''),
(125, 21, 'SCPI command for the Stamp3PlugInLoadGalaxy.vi', 4, '2010-11-18 09:37:34', '<p><strong><u>SCPI command for the Stamp3PlugInLoadGalaxy.vi</u></strong></p><p><strong><u>Init the plug-in</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">WAGO750_IO_LOAD</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">WAGO750_IO_LOAD</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Label of Digital Input Output plug-in used to dive physically the load <em>(ex: WAGO 750 IO SYSTEM)</em> &nbsp;</font></p><p><br /><strong><u>Reset the load</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">RST:</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">RST:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Execute the macro-command designed to reset the load <em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro RST line)</em></font><br />&nbsp;<br /><strong><u>Apply Power</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:POWER:</font>(<font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>,<font color=\"#0000ff\">Power</font>,<font color=\"#008000\">PH1,PH2,PH3</font><font color=\"#000000\">)</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:POWER</font>: <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Apply Power</font></p><p><font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Define the type of load. Use:</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'R\',&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RC\', </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RL\' or </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RDC\'&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\"> </font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">Power</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Power need <em>(float value)</em>&nbsp;</font><br /><font color=\"#008000\">PHx=</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Balancing <em>(in % of total power)</em> ex: (RL,1000.0,33.333,33.333,33.333) to apply a same power on each phase <em>(333.33 VA)</em>&nbsp;</font><br />&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Apply Short-Circuit</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:SHORT:</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:SHORT:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Execute the macro-command designed to realize the Short-Circuit <em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro C/C line)</em></font></p>&nbsp;<p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Set Frequency</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:FREQ: </font><font color=\"#ff00ff\">xxHZ</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:FREQ:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Execute the macro-command designed to set the load frequency</font></p><p><font color=\"#ff00ff\">xxHZ</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Define the frequency. Use:</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'50HZ\'</font><font color=\"#808080\"> or </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'60HZ\' </font><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;<em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro Switch xxHZ lines)</em></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Apply Steps</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:STEP:</font>(<font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>,<font color=\"#008000\">PH1,PH2,PH3</font><font color=\"#000000\">)</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:STEP:</font> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Apply Steps</font></p><p><font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Define the type of load. Use:</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'R\',&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RC\', </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RL\' or </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RDC\'&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\"> </font></p><p><font color=\"#008000\">PHx=</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Set at \'1\' the load step need to use <em>(12 step by phase)</em> ex: (RL,100011001110,111111111111,000000000000) to apply 6 steps on PH1, 12 on PH2 and 0 on PH3&nbsp;</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Read Status</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">GET:STAT?</font> <font color=\"#008000\">~(IN1,IN2,IN3)~</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">GET:STAT?</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; </font><font color=\"#808080\">Execute the macro-command designed to read the load status <em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro Status line)</em></font><br /><font color=\"#008000\">~(x)~</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; List of variable label to be assigned in the same order as the inputs, separated by coma</font>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ''),
