(130, 4, '1st step - Connect the network disks \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'', 4, '2010-08-16 17:06:03', '<strong><u>1st step - Connect the network disks &nbsp;\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\':</u></strong><br /><br /><u><strong>Setup the \'Q\' disk:</strong></u><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>Q</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Quasar</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup the \'S\' disk:</u></strong><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>S</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Stamp3</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup the \'T\' disk:</u></strong><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>T</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Test</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Checking:</u></strong><br />A window is automatically opened at the end of each setup. The new network disc data are displayed<br /><br /><u><strong>Remarks:</strong></u><br />Use only the \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as Qasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters to identify the network disks', '', ''),
(131, 4, '1st step - Connect the network disks \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'', 5, '2010-11-23 13:52:06', '<strong><u>1st step - Connect the network&nbsp;drives&nbsp;&nbsp;\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\':</u></strong><br /><br /><u><strong>Setup the \'Q\' disk:</strong></u><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>Q</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Quasar</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup the \'S\' disk:</u></strong><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>S</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Stamp3</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup the \'T\' disk:</u></strong><br />Open the files manager. In \'Tools\' menu, select \'Connected a network disc\'<br />Select the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\"><strong>T</strong></font>\' letter to name the disc<br />Write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\www\\Test</font>\' as network path<br />Select the option \'reopen when opening session\'<br />Click on \'Connected on the other user identifying\'<br />As user name write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">indus</font>\' and for password write \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">test</font>\'<br /><br /><strong><u>Checking:</u></strong><br />A window is automatically opened at the 