(132, 4, '1st step - Connect the network disks \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'', 5, '2010-11-23 14:02:57', '<p><strong><u>1st step - Connect the network&nbsp;drives&nbsp;&nbsp;\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\':</u></strong><br /><br /><u><strong>Setup the \'Q\' disk:</strong></u><br />Create a new text document.</p><p>Insert the following lines :</p><p>Net USE Q: <a href=\"../../Quasar\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\Quasar</a> apcmge09 /user:indus<br />Net USE S: <a href=\"../../Stamp3\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\Stamp3</a> apcmge09 /user:indus<br />Net USE T: <a href=\"../../Test\">\\\\10.216.20.101\\Test</a> apcmge09 /user:indus</p><p>Save the file as <font color=\"#000000\">\'</font><font color=\"#0000c0\">ConnectNetworkDrives.bat</font><font color=\"#000000\">\'.</font></p><p>Drag the created file to the <font color=\"#0000ff\">Start menu</font>, and hold it until the menu opens. With the mouse left button still held down, move over the <font color=\"#0000ff\">All programs</font> selection until the menu opens. When the <font color=\"#0000ff\">Program menu</font> opens, drop the file to the start menu by releasing the mouse left button.</p><p><strong><u>Checking:</u></strong><br />A consol command&nbsp;window is automatically opened each time the file is executed. The new network drives are then available.<br /><br /><u><strong>Remarks:</strong></u><br />Use only the \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as Quasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters to identify the network disks</p>', 'Mount_QSXY.bat', ''),
