(166, 4, '[Stamp setup] 1st step - Connect the network drives \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'', 4, '2010-11-24 17:30:03', '<p><strong><u>[Stamp setup] 1st step - Connect the network&nbsp;drives&nbsp;&nbsp;\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\':</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Usage:</u></strong></p><p>The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>Q</strong>uasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters are used to identify the network drives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Setup:</strong></u></p><p>First, download and save the file <font color=\"#0000ff\"><a href=\"../doc/ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\" title=\"ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\">CopyConnectNetworkDrives.bat</a> </font><font color=\"#000000\">to <strong>C:\\</strong> and double click on it&nbsp;</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Run the installation program located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\01. CopyConnectNetworkDrives.bat</font>\'.</p>', '', ''),
(167, 25, '[STAMP SETUP] 1st step: Check that the drive letters are available', 5, '2010-11-25 08:47:12', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 1st step - Check taht the drive letters are available<br /></u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br /><u><strong>Opening remark:</strong></u></p><p><br />The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' (as <u><strong>Q</strong></u>uasar), \'<strong>S</strong>\' (as <u><strong>S</strong></u>tamp) and \'<strong>T</strong>\' (as <u><strong>T</strong></u>est) drive letters are necessary to use Stamp 3.&nbsp; </p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p><u><strong><br /></strong></u>Open the Windows Explorer and check that the \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' drive letters are available.<br />If not, the given drive letters must be unmapped in order to use Stamp3.<u><strong><br /><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p>Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives</p>', '', ''),
(168, 25, '[STAMP SETUP] 1st step: Check that the drive letters are available', 5, '2010-11-25 08:47:31', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 1st step - Check that the drive letters are available<br /></u></strong></p><p><br /><u><strong>Opening remark:</strong></u></p><p><br />The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' (as <u><strong>Q</strong></u>uasar), \'<strong>S</strong>\' (as <u><strong>S</strong></u>tamp) and \'<strong>T</strong>\' (as <u><strong>T</strong></u>est) drive letters are necessary to use Stamp 3.&nbsp; </p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p><u><strong><br /></strong></u>Open the Windows Explorer and check that the \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' drive letters are available.<br />If not, the given drive letters must be unmapped in order to use Stamp3.<u><strong><br /><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p>Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives</p>', '', ''),
(169, 25, '[STAMP SETUP] 1st step: Check that the drive letters are available', 5, '2010-11-25 08:47:49', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 1st step - Check that the drive letters are available<br /></u></strong></p><p><br /><u><strong>Opening remark:</strong></u></p><p><br />The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' (as <u><strong>Q</strong></u>uasar), \'<strong>S</strong>\' (as <u><strong>S</strong></u>tamp) and \'<strong>T</strong>\' (as <u><strong>T</strong></u>est) drive letters are necessary to use Stamp 3.&nbsp; </p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p><u><strong><br /></strong></u>Open the Windows Explorer and check that the \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' drive letters are available.<br />If not, the given drive letters must be unmapped in order to use Stamp3.<u><strong><br /><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p>Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives</p>', '', ''),
(170, 26, '[STAMP SETUP] 2nd step: Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives', 5, '2010-11-25 08:49:48', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 2nd step - Map the </u></strong><strong><u>\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\' </u></strong><strong><u>network&nbsp;drives </u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Opening remark:</u></strong></p><p>The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>Q</strong>uasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters are used to identify the network drives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p>Download and execute the file <font color=\"#0000ff\"><a href=\"../doc/ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\" title=\"ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\">ConnectNetworkDrives.bat</a></font><font color=\"#000000\">. <br /></font></p><p>Once the file is executed, open the Windows Explorer and check that the three network drives have been successfully mapped<br />(click on each letter to check that you can access to the corresponding network drive)<br /></p>', '', ''),
