(214, 26, '[STAMP SETUP] 2nd step: Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives', 5, '2010-11-25 10:40:52', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 2nd step - Map the </u></strong><strong><u>\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\' </u></strong><strong><u>network&nbsp;drives </u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Opening remark:</u></strong></p><p>The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>Q</strong>uasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters are used to identify the network drives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p>Download and execute the file <font color=\"#0000ff\"><a href=\"../doc/ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\" title=\"ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\">ConnectNetworkDrives.bat</a></font><font color=\"#000000\">. <br /></font></p><p>Once the file is executed, open the Windows Explorer and check that the three network drives have been successfully mapped<br />(click on each letter to check that you can access to the corresponding network drive).</p><p><u><strong><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=27\">Install Stamp 3 (automatic mode)</a> or <a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=28\">Install Stamp 3 (manual mode) </a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ''),
