(223, 22, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 3rd step - Install the VISA runtime', 5, '2010-11-25 10:39:26', '<p><u><strong>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE]</strong></u><strong><u> 3rd step - Install the VISA runtime<br /></u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u>Setup:</u></p><p>Run the installation program located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\04_InstallVISAruntime.exe</font>\'.<br /><br /><u>Remarks:</u><br />This setup program is a standard program. Use all standard answers</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong><br />Next step:</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=23\">Install STAMP3</a> </p>', '', ''),
(224, 5, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE]  2nd step - Install and Setup the ODBC Server', 5, '2010-11-25 10:40:07', '<p><u><strong>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] </strong></u><strong><u>2nd step - Install and Setup the ODBC Server</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Install the ODBC Server:</u></strong></p><p><u>Setup:</u></p><p>Run the msi file located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\02_InstallODBCDriver.msi</font>\'. </p><p><br /><u>Remarks:</u><br />This setup program is a standard program. Use all standard answers<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup theODBC Server:</u></strong><br /><u>Setup:</u><br />Run the reg file located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\03_CreateODBCdataSourceNames</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">.reg</font>\'.<br /><br /><u>Test:</u></p><p>On the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">start</font>\' menu, choose <font color=\"#0000ff\">\'administrative tools</font>\', and click on <font color=\"#0000ff\">\'Data sources (ODBC)</font>\'.<br />If the installation has succeeded, 6 new data sources must have been created : <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3ate</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3drv</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3inst</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3qua</font>, and <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3uut</font>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Select the data source you want to check. Click on the configuration button to see the data source informations. The data source information must be filled in accordance with the following table :</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><table border=\"1\" align=\"center\"><thead><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Base 1</strong></td><td>&nbsp;<strong>Base 2</strong></td><td><strong>Base 3&nbsp;</strong></td><td><strong>Base 4</strong>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Base 5&nbsp;</strong></td><td><strong>Base 6 </strong>&nbsp;</td></tr></thead><caption><br /></caption><tbody><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Data source name</strong></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3ate</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3drv</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3inst</font></td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3uut</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3qua</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Description</strong></td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3</td><td>&nbsp;Ate database</td><td>&nbsp;Driver database</td><td>&nbsp;Instrument parameters</td><td>&nbsp;UUT database</td><td>&nbsp;Quality database</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Server</strong></td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Port <em>(if need)</em></strong></td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;User</strong></td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Password</strong></td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Database <em>(select)</em></strong></td><td>&nbsp;stamp3</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3ate</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3drv</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3inst</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3uut</td><td>&nbsp;dicotrack</td></tr></tbody></table></p><p align=\"left\"><br /><u>Remark:</u><br />It&rsquo;s possible to use the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Test</font>\' button to check the access&nbsp;to the MySQL database</p><p><u><strong><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=22\">Install the VISA runtime<br /></a></p>', '', ''),
(225, 4, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 1st step - Connect the network drives \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'', 5, '2010-11-25 10:40:21', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 1st step - Connect the network&nbsp;drives&nbsp;&nbsp;\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\':</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Usage:</u></strong></p><p>The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>Q</strong>uasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters are used to identify the network drives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Setup:</u></strong></p>Run the installation program located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\01_CopyConnectNetworkDrives.bat</font>\'. <p><u><strong><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=5\">Install and Setup the ODBC Server</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', ''),
