(229, 25, '[STAMP SETUP] 1st step: Check that the drive letters are available', 5, '2010-11-25 10:41:01', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 1st step - Check that the drive letters are available<br /></u></strong></p><p><br /><u><strong>Opening remark:</strong></u></p><p><br />The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' (as <u><strong>Q</strong></u>uasar), \'<strong>S</strong>\' (as <u><strong>S</strong></u>tamp) and \'<strong>T</strong>\' (as <u><strong>T</strong></u>est) drive letters are necessary to use Stamp 3.&nbsp; </p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p><u><strong><br /></strong></u>Open the Windows Explorer and check that the \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' drive letters are available.<br />If not, the given drive letters must be unmapped in order to use Stamp3.<u><strong><br /><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=26\">Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives</a></p>', '', ''),
