(1, 'Wizard XML file format description', 4, '2010-08-17 13:06:29', '<p><strong><u>XML format for the Wizard Plug-in descriptor</u></strong><br />All the examples are issued from the SCPI parameter command into the HP 34970 instrument &sect;5<br />Note 1: the order of parameter have an importance to constitute easily the list of parameters<br />Note 2: to write the New Line command like  write: <font color=\"#ff0000\">&lt;</font>NL<font color=\"#ff0000\">&gt;</font> &rarr; <font color=\"#ff0000\">&amp;lt;</font>NL<font color=\"#ff0000\">&amp;gt;</font></p><p><br /><strong><u>Global structure</u></strong></p><font color=\"#ff0000\"><p><strong><font color=\"#000000\">wizard</font></strong></p><blockquote><font color=\"#800000\">header<br /></font></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#800000\">/header</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#333399\">instrument<br /></font></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#333399\">/instrument</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#ff0000\">functions</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#808000\">function name=&quot;&quot;</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#008000\">parameters</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#0000ff\">parameter label=&quot;&quot;<br /></font></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#0000ff\">/parameter</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#008000\">/parameters</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#808000\">/function</font><br /></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><font color=\"#ff0000\">/functions</font><br /></blockquote></font><strong><font color=\"#000000\">/wizard</font></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Header structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><br /><font color=\"#800000\"><strong>header</strong></font><br /><blockquote>program  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; alway </font><font color=\"#800080\">Stamp3</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>function  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; alway </font><font color=\"#800080\">Plug-in</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; example: HP 34970 A</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>module <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; use the name of the VI <em>(plug-in)</em> associated with this XML file</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>use  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; BASIC_PANEL if standard or the path of the specific panel.vi to be used</font>&nbsp;<br /></blockquote><font color=\"#800000\"><strong>/header</strong></font><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Instrument structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"> <br /><font color=\"#333399\"><strong>instrument</strong></font><br /><blockquote>supplier  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; name of the instrument supplier</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>reference  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; instrument reference like: HP34970A</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>who  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; who have created this XML parameters</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>when  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; When this XML document has created</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>revision  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Revision of this document</font> <br /></blockquote><font color=\"#333399\"><strong>/instrument</strong></font><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Functions structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><br />List of instruments <font color=\"#808000\">function</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Include all the functions describe for the instrument</font><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Function structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"> <br /><font color=\"#808000\"><strong>function name=&quot;&quot;</strong></font></font><font color=\"#000000\">&nbsp;&rarr;  use an unique label to identify the instrument function like: MEASure:VOLTage:DC&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#ff0000\"><br /><blockquote>label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like MEAS:VOLT:DC</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; global format to describe the SCPI command with one \'%s\' like: &quot;MEAS:VOLT:DC? %s</font>&amp;lt;<font color=\"#808080\">NL</font>&amp;gt;<font color=\"#808080\">&quot;</font></blockquote><blockquote>parameters &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; the entry of parameters list <em>(the parameters data replace dynamically the %s into the command format)</em></font> <br /></blockquote><font color=\"#808000\"><strong>/function</strong></font><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Parameters structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"><br /></font><font color=\"#000000\">List of function</font><font color=\"#ff0000\"> <font color=\"#008000\">parameter</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Include all the parameter describe for the function</font><br /><br /></font><strong><u><font color=\"#000000\">Parameter structure</font></u></strong><font color=\"#ff0000\"> <br /><font color=\"#008000\"><strong>parameter</strong></font><strong><font color=\"#008000\"> </font><font color=\"#008000\">label=&quot;&quot;</font></strong> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; use an unique label to identify the parameter into a function like: Auto</font><br /><blockquote>type  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; type for parameter. select: INT or REAL or BOOL or STRING or LIST or SWITCH or SW_EXT</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote>need  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; if true the parameter is alway need. if false the operator can select to use or not the parameter</font><br /></blockquote><blockquote><em>parameters</em> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; depending of type, see TYPE parameter description</font></blockquote><p><font color=\"#008000\"><strong>/parameter</strong></font><br /><br /><u><strong><font color=\"#000000\">TYPE parameter description</font></strong></u><br /><br /><strong><font color=\"#000000\">INT</font></strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_int.jpg\" alt=\"XML INT\" width=\"196\" height=\"82\" />&nbsp;</p><p>mini &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; minimal value accepted</font><br />maxi  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; maximal value accepted</font><br />default  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting</font><br />unit  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like V, mA, Hz, ...</font><br />format  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like %d, %03d,... used to convert the integer into a string</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;CLOS (@%s)&quot; used in global SCPI command ROUT:CLOS ()</font><br /><br /><strong><font color=\"#000000\">REAL</font></strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_real.jpg\" alt=\"XML REAL\" width=\"192\" height=\"82\" /></p><p>mini &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; minimal value accepted</font><br />maxi  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; maximal value accepted</font><br />default  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting</font><br />unit  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like V, mA, Hz</font><br />format  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; like %f, %3.1f,... used to convert the real value into a string</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;GAIN %s&quot; used in global SCPI command SCAL:GAIN</font> <br /><br /><strong><font color=\"#000000\">BOOL</font></strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_bool.jpg\" alt=\"XML BOOL\" width=\"192\" height=\"80\" /></p><p>command &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;:AUTO %s&quot; used in global SCPI command RANGE:AUTO {OFF|ON}</font><br />label_true  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; true label displayed like: Auto = ON</font><br />command_true  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; string used for the true selection like: ON</font><br />label_false  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; false label displayed like: Auto = OFF</font><br />command_false <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; string used for the false selection like: OFF</font><br /><br /><strong><font color=\"#000000\">STRING</font></strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_string.jpg\" alt=\"XML STRING\" width=\"195\" height=\"80\" /></p><p>default &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;:TEXT \\&quot;%s\\&quot; used in global SCPI command DISPlay:TEXT</font> <br /><br /><strong><font color=\"#000000\">LIST</font></strong></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_list.jpg\" alt=\"XML LIST\" width=\"193\" height=\"81\" /></p><p>command &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;:BAND %s&quot; used in global SCPI command VOLTage:AC:BANDwidth {3|20|200|MIN|MAX}</font><br />default  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; default value setting like: 1 to select 20 (index start at 0)</font></p><p>Item_Nbr &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; number of items in the list</font></p><p>Items  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; container of items list</font><br />Item_01  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label &amp; command used for the 1st item</font><br />Item_02  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label &amp; command used for the 2nd item</font><br />... ... ...<br />Item_nn  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label &amp; command used for the last item</font><br /><br /><font color=\"#000000\"><strong>SWITCH</strong> and <strong>SW_EX</strong></font></p><p><img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_switch.jpg\" alt=\"XML SWITCH\" width=\"194\" height=\"79\" /></p><p>state0label &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label on middle position like: O</font><br />state0value  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; value on middle position like: O</font><br />state1label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label on low position like: L</font><br />state1value  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; value on low position like: L</font><br />state2label  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; label on high position like: H</font><br />state2value  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; value on high position like: H</font><br />command  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command format with one \'%s\' ex: &quot;SQ%s&quot; used as command line for the QuadCheck 7564A SQLHHOOOOO</font></p></font><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>OFF</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;<img src=\"../images/custom/xml_img/xml_off.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"191\" height=\"80\" /></p><p><font color=\"#ff0000\">command</font> &nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; alway free</font></p><p><u>Note:</u> The <strong>OFF</strong> type is used when a function need no parameter&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(2, 'SCPI command for the Stamp3PlugInWAGO750visa.vi', 4, '2010-08-16 16:31:54', '<p><strong><u>SCPI command for the Stamp3PlugInWAGO750visa.vi</u></strong><br /><br /><strong><u>Init the plug-in</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">ASRL1::INSTR</font>(<font color=\"#0000ff\">1,19200,2500</font>)<br /><font color=\"#800000\">ASRL1::INSTR</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; VISA label</font><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">1</font> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Slave address</font><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">19200</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Baud-rate</font><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">2500</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Timeout</font><br /><br /><strong><u>Reset all coils</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">OPEN:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">ALL</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">OPEN:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command</font><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">ALL</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; all the 256 coils <em>(from 0 to 255)</em></font><br /><br /><strong><u>Set coils <em>(Dynamic controls)</em></u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">DOUT:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">C=0,2</font>|<font color=\"#008000\">O=1,4,6,8</font>|<font color=\"#ff00ff\">D=1.0</font>|<font color=\"#0000ff\">C=1,4,6,8</font>|<font color=\"#008000\">O=0,2</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">DOUT:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command</font><br /><em><font color=\"#993300\">The actions are interpreted from left to right. The actions are separated by the vertical bar \':\' without any space!</font></em><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">C=</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Close the list of coils address, separated by coma</font><br /><font color=\"#008000\">O=</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Open the list of coils address, separated by coma</font><br /><font color=\"#ff00ff\">D=</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Wait a delay in second</font><br /><br /><strong><u>Read coils <em>(To variables)</em></u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">DIN:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">0,2,4</font> <font color=\"#008000\">~(IN1,IN2,IN3)~</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">DIN:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Command</font><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">0,2,4</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; List of input address to be read, separated by coma</font><br /><font color=\"#008000\">~(x)~</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; List of variable label to be assigned in the same order as the inputs, separated by coma</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(3, 'Enhanced SCPI description', 4, '2010-10-15 10:23:32', '<p><strong><u>Enhanced SCPI description</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;<img src=\"../images/custom/mindmap/scpi.png\" alt=\"SCPI\" width=\"1418\" height=\"4873\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(4, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 1st step - Connect the network drives \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'', 5, '2010-11-25 13:59:32', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 1st step - Connect the network&nbsp;drives&nbsp;&nbsp;\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\':</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Usage:</u></strong></p><p>The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>Q</strong>uasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters are used to identify the network drives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Setup:</u></strong></p>Run the installation program located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\01_CopyConnectNetworkDrives.bat</font>\'. <p><u><strong><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=5\">Install and Setup the ODBC Server</a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(5, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE]  2nd step - Install and Setup the ODBC Server', 5, '2010-11-25 13:59:17', '<p><u><strong>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] </strong></u><strong><u>2nd step - Install and Setup the ODBC Server</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Install the ODBC Server:</u></strong></p><p><u>Setup:</u></p><p>Run the msi file located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\02_InstallODBCDriver.msi</font>\'. </p><p><br /><u>Remarks:</u><br />This setup program is a standard program. Use all standard answers<br /><br /><strong><u>Setup theODBC Server:</u></strong><br /><u>Setup:</u><br />Run the reg file located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\03_CreateODBCdataSourceNames</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">.reg</font>\'.<br /><br /><u>Test:</u></p><p>On the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">start</font>\' menu, choose <font color=\"#0000ff\">\'administrative tools</font>\', and click on <font color=\"#0000ff\">\'Data sources (ODBC)</font>\'.<br />If the installation has succeeded, 6 new data sources must have been created : <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3ate</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3drv</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3inst</font>, <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3qua</font>, and <font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3uut</font>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Select the data source you want to check. Click on the configuration button to see the data source informations. The data source information must be filled in accordance with the following table :</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><table border=\"1\" align=\"center\"><thead><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Base 1</strong></td><td>&nbsp;<strong>Base 2</strong></td><td><strong>Base 3&nbsp;</strong></td><td><strong>Base 4</strong>&nbsp;</td><td><strong>Base 5&nbsp;</strong></td><td><strong>Base 6 </strong>&nbsp;</td></tr></thead><caption><br /></caption><tbody><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Data source name</strong></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3ate</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3drv</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3inst</font></td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3uut</font></td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#0000ff\">stamp3qua</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Description</strong></td><td>&nbsp;Stamp3</td><td>&nbsp;Ate database</td><td>&nbsp;Driver database</td><td>&nbsp;Instrument parameters</td><td>&nbsp;UUT database</td><td>&nbsp;Quality database</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Server</strong></td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td><td>&nbsp;10.216.20.101</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Port <em>(if need)</em></strong></td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td><td>&nbsp;3306</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;User</strong></td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td><td>&nbsp;indus</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<strong>Password</strong></td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td><td>&nbsp;test</td></tr><tr><td><strong>&nbsp;Database <em>(select)</em></strong></td><td>&nbsp;stamp3</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3ate</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3drv</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3inst</td><td>&nbsp;stamp3uut</td><td>&nbsp;dicotrack</td></tr></tbody></table></p><p align=\"left\"><br /><u>Remark:</u><br />It&rsquo;s possible to use the \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">Test</font>\' button to check the access&nbsp;to the MySQL database</p><p><u><strong><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=22\">Install the VISA runtime<br /></a></p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(6, 'SCPI commands for the ASCII plug-in (Stamp3PlugInASCII.vi)', 5, '2010-10-26 09:01:25', '<p><strong><u>SCPI commands for the ASCII plug-in (Stamp3PlugInASCII.vi</u></strong>)</p><br /><p>&nbsp;<u><strong>1. Plug-in setting : </strong></u></p><blockquote><p>This section gives all the SCPI commands necessary to the serial port configuration. </p></blockquote><blockquote><p><em><u>1.1. Initialization :</u></em></p><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">COMx:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">9600,8</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"174\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"height: 24px; width: 80px\">&nbsp;Explanation : </td><td style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#800000\">COMx</font></td><td style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Serial port </font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">9600</font>&nbsp; <br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Baud rate (bits/s)</font> </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">8</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Data bits</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Parity (0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;odd&quot;, 2 : &quot;even&quot;, 3 : &quot;mark&quot;, 4 : &quot;space&quot;)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">1</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Timeout (ms)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Flow control (</font><font color=\"#808080\">0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;XON/XOFF&quot;, 2 : &quot;RTS/CTS&quot;, 3 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">RTS/CTS</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;,</font><font color=\"#808080\"> 4 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;, </font><font color=\"#808080\">5 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote><p><em><u>1.2. Change serial port settings :</u></em> </p><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:SET(</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">9600,8</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"70\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">9600</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Baud rate (bits/s)</font> </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">8</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Data bits</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Parity (0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;odd&quot;, 2 : &quot;even&quot;, 3 : &quot;mark&quot;, 4 : &quot;space&quot;)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">10</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 537px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Stop bits (</font><font color=\"#808080\">10 : &quot;1.0 bits&quot;,&nbsp; </font><font color=\"#808080\">15 : &quot;1.5 bits&quot;, </font><font color=\"#808080\">20 : &quot;2.0 bits&quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> <p><em><u>1.2. Synchronize serial port :</u></em> </p><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:SYNC(<font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,CR</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"70\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Flow control (</font><font color=\"#808080\">0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;XON/XOFF&quot;, 2 : &quot;RTS/CTS&quot;, 3 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">RTS/CTS</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;,</font><font color=\"#808080\"> 4 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;, </font><font color=\"#808080\">5 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font> </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">CR</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Termination char </font><font color=\"#808080\">(\'CR\', \'LF\', \'CRLF\'</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">1</font><br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Timeout (ms)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">10</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 537px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Rate (ms)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> <p><em><u>1.4. Open serial port :</u></em> </p> </blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:OPEN()</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote><p><em><u>1.5. Close serial port :</u></em></p></blockquote>  <blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:CLOSE()</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></blockquote><p>&nbsp;<u><strong>2</strong><strong>. Send data :</strong></u></p><blockquote>This section gives all the available SCPI commands to send data to the unit under test via the serial port.&nbsp; <br /></blockquote><blockquote><em><font color=\"#999999\">Note : For each data type (order, parameter, string, file), the &quot;</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#999999\">&quot; parameter refers to the definition of the data, made in the STAMP settings (the label being linked to the product address where the data will be written). </font></em></blockquote><blockquote><em><u>2.1. Order :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote> <blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:SEND:ORDER(<font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL</font></font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Order label</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>2.2. Parameter :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:SEND:</font><font color=\"#800000\">PARAM</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,VALUE</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0