ble></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>4.4. File :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:CFILE</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,PATH</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">File label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Path of the file that contains the list of the parameters to read, and the expected values</font><br /></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><p><strong><u>5. File infos</u></strong></p><blockquote><p>&nbsp;With the ASCII plugin, it\'s possible to read, send or check a list of values given in a file (whose path is given in the <font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></font> parameter).</p><p>The following example gives an overview of the informations that can be found in this kind of file : </p><p><font color=\"#999999\">[UUT_DESCRIPTION]<br />serial =UUT_SERIAL</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">reference = UUT_REF<br />date = MM/DD/YYYY<br />time = HH:MM:SS</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">path_template = path/to/the/template.ini</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\"><br />[PARAMETERS]<br />post_delay = 0.5<br /><br />[SETTINGS]<br />SET_U_UTIL = 230.0<br />SET_U_BATT = 100.0<br />etc.</font></p><p>The first section (<font color=\"#999999\">UUT_DESCRIPTION</font>) gives the global informations relative to the unit under test.</p><p>The second section (<font color=\"#999999\">PARAMETERS</font>) sets the plugin parameter.The &quot;<font color=\"#999999\">post_delay</font>&quot;   parameter sets the wait time (in seconds) when reading or sending   parameters. It must be adapted to the unit under test time response   (default value : 0.5 second). </p><p>The last section (<font color=\"#999999\">SETTINGS</font>) lists all the parameters that will be read, sent or check in the unit under test.</p></blockquote>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(21, 'SCPI command for the Stamp3PlugInLoadGalaxy.vi', 4, '2010-11-18 09:46:39', '<p><strong><u>SCPI command for the Stamp3PlugInLoadGalaxy.vi</u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Init the plug-in</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">WAGO750_IO_LOAD</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">WAGO750_IO_LOAD</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Label of Digital Input Output plug-in used to dive physically the load <em>(ex: WAGO 750 IO SYSTEM)</em> &nbsp;</font></p><p><br /><strong><u>Reset the load</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">RST:</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font><br /><font color=\"#0000ff\">RST:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Execute the macro-command designed to reset the load <em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro RST line)</em></font><br />&nbsp;<br /><strong><u>Apply Power</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:POWER:</font>(<font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>,<font color=\"#0000ff\">Power</font>,<font color=\"#008000\">PH1,PH2,PH3</font><font color=\"#000000\">)</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:POWER</font>: <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Apply Power</font></p><p><font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Define the type of load. Use:</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'R\',&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RC\', </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RL\' or </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RDC\'&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\"> </font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">Power</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Power need <em>(float value)</em>&nbsp;</font><br /><font color=\"#008000\">PHx=</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Balancing <em>(in % of total power)</em> ex: (RL,1000.0,33.333,33.333,33.333) to apply a same power on each phase <em>(333.33 VA)</em>&nbsp;</font><br />&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Apply Short-Circuit</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:SHORT:</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:SHORT:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Execute the macro-command designed to realize the Short-Circuit <em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro C/C line)</em></font></p>&nbsp;<p><strong><u>Set Frequency</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:FREQ: </font><font color=\"#ff00ff\">xxHZ</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:FREQ:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Execute the macro-command designed to set the load frequency</font></p><p><font color=\"#ff00ff\">xxHZ</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Define the frequency. Use:</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'50HZ\'</font><font color=\"#808080\"> or </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'60HZ\' </font><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;<em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro Switch xxHZ lines)</em></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Apply Steps</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:STEP:</font>(<font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>,<font color=\"#008000\">PH1,PH2,PH3</font><font color=\"#000000\">)</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font></p><p><font color=\"#0000ff\">SET:STEP:</font> <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Apply Steps</font></p><p><font color=\"#ff00ff\">Type</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Define the type of load. Use:</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'R\',&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RC\', </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RL\' or </font><font color=\"#808080\">\'RDC\'&nbsp;</font><font color=\"#808080\"> </font></p><p><font color=\"#008000\">PHx=</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Set at \'1\' the load step need to use <em>(12 step by phase)</em> ex: (RL,100011001110,111111111111,000000000000) to apply 6 steps on PH1, 12 on PH2 and 0 on PH3&nbsp;</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Read Status</u></strong><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">GET:STAT?</font> <font color=\"#008000\">~(IN1,IN2,IN3)~</font><br /><font color=\"#800000\">LOAD:</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; Load action</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">GET:STAT?</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; </font><font color=\"#808080\">Execute the macro-command designed to read the load status <em>(see table in [Station|Plug-in|Instrument|Load] at Macro Status line)</em></font><br /><font color=\"#008000\">~(x)~</font>  <font color=\"#808080\">&rarr; List of variable label to be assigned in the same order as the inputs, separated by coma</font>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Example of parameters table:</u></strong></p><p><strong></strong>&nbsp;<img src=\"../images/custom/plug-in/TableLoadGalaxy.jpg\" alt=\"TableLoadGalaxy\" width=\"836\" height=\"670\" /></p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(22, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 3rd step - Install the VISA runtime', 5, '2010-11-25 13:58:59', '<p><u><strong>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE]</strong></u><strong><u> 3rd step - Install the VISA runtime<br /></u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u>Setup:</u></p><p>Run the installation program located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\04_InstallVISAruntime.exe</font>\'.<br /><br /><u>Remarks:</u><br />This setup program is a standard program. Use all standard answers</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong><br />Next step:</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=23\">Install STAMP3</a> </p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(23, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 4th step - Install the Stamp3 application', 5, '2010-11-25 13:58:51', '<p><u><strong>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE]</strong></u><strong> </strong><strong><u>4th step - Install the Stamp3 application<br /></u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u>Setup:</u></p><p>Run the installation program located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\05_InstallSTAMP3.exe</font>\'.<br /><br /><u>Remarks:</u><br />This setup program is a standard program. Use all standard answers</p><p><u><strong><br />Next step:</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=24\">Copy Plugin directory</a> </p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(24, '[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 5th step - Copy the Plugin directory', 5, '2010-11-25 13:58:39', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP - MANUAL MODE] 5th step - Copy the Plugin directory<br /></u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u>Setup:</u></p>Run the installation program located on \'<font color=\"#0000ff\">T:\\stamp3setup\\06_CopyPluginDirectory.bat</font>\'.', '', '', 0, 't'),
(25, '[STAMP SETUP] 1st step: Check that the drive letters are available', 5, '2010-11-25 14:00:13', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 1st step - Check that the drive letters are available<br /></u></strong></p><p><br /><u><strong>Opening remark:</strong></u></p><p><br />The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' (as <u><strong>Q</strong></u>uasar), \'<strong>S</strong>\' (as <u><strong>S</strong></u>tamp) and \'<strong>T</strong>\' (as <u><strong>T</strong></u>est) drive letters are necessary to use Stamp 3.&nbsp; </p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p><u><strong><br /></strong></u>Open the Windows Explorer and check that the \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' drive letters are available.<br />If not, the given drive letters must be unmapped in order to use Stamp3.<u><strong><br /><br />Next step :</strong></u></p><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=26\">Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives</a></p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(26, '[STAMP SETUP] 2nd step: Map The \'Q\', \'S\' and \'T\' network drives', 5, '2010-11-25 14:00:05', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 2nd step - Map the </u></strong><strong><u>\'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\' </u></strong><strong><u>network&nbsp;drives </u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Opening remark:</u></strong></p><p>The \'<strong>Q</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>Q</strong>uasar)</em>, \'<strong>S</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>S</strong>tamp)</em> and \'<strong>T</strong>\' <em>(as <strong>T</strong>est)</em> letters are used to identify the network drives.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Process help:</strong></u></p><p>Download and execute the file <font color=\"#0000ff\"><a href=\"../doc/ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\" title=\"ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\">ConnectNetworkDrives.bat</a></font><font color=\"#000000\">. <br /></font></p><p>Once the file is executed, open the Windows Explorer and check that the three network drives have been successfully mapped<br />(click on each letter to check that you can access to the corresponding network drive).</p><p><u><strong><br />Next step:</strong></u></p><p><font color=\"#000000\"><font color=\"#363636\">Choose the installation method you want to use:</font></font></p><font color=\"#000000\"><p><table border=\"0\" style=\"width: 702px; height: 56px\"><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;<u>1. Full automatic method:</u> </td><td><font color=\"#000000\">Download and execute the file&nbsp;</font><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=27\">Install Stamp 3 (automatic mode)</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;<u>2. Manual step-by-step installation:</u> </td><td>Download and execute the file&nbsp;<a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=28\">Install Stamp 3 (manual mode) </a></td></tr></tbody></table></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Remark:</strong></u></p><p>The manual installation enables you to have a better comprehension.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></font><p><a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=28\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(27, '[STAMP SETUP] 3rd step: Install Stamp 3 (automatic mode)', 5, '2010-11-25 13:59:53', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 3rd step - Install Stamp 3 (automatic mode)<br /></u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Process help:</u></strong></p><p>Download and execute&nbsp; the file <a href=\"T:/stamp3setup/00_InstallStamp3.bat\" title=\"ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\"></a><font color=\"#0000ff\"><a href=\"../doc/InstallStamp3.bat\" title=\"ConnectNetworkDrives.bat\">InstallStamp3.bat</a></font><font color=\"#0000ff\">.</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><u><strong>Remark:</strong></u></p><p>This setup program is a standard program. Use all standard answers.</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(28, '[STAMP SETUP] 3rd step: Install Stamp 3 (manual mode)', 5, '2010-11-25 13:59:44', '<p><strong><u>[STAMP SETUP] 3rd step - Install Stamp 3 (manual mode)<br /></u></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><u>Process help:</u></strong></p><p><br />1. <a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=4\">Connect the network drives \'Q\', \'S\' &amp; \'T\'</a></p><p>2. <a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=5\">Install and Setup the ODBC Server</a></p><p>3. <a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=22\">Install the VISA runtime</a></p><p>4. <a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=23\">Install the Stamp3 application</a></p><p>5. <a href=\"document_show.php?document_id=24\">Copy the Plugin directory</a></p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(29, 'ATE - G2000 - Auto Transformer Variable 40kVA', 4, '2010-11-30 08:01:48', '<p><font size=\"7\"><strong><font color=\"#993300\">ATE</font></strong></font></p><p><strong><font size=\"6\">G2000</font></strong></p><p><strong><font size=\"6\">Auto Transformer Variable 40kVA</font></strong></p><p><font size=\"3\"><a href=\"../doc/instrument/ate/G2000/Auto Transfo Variable 40KVA G2000.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"ATE - G2000 - Auto Transformer Variable 40kVA\">ATE - G2000 - Auto Transformer Variable 40kVA</a></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(30, 'COMM - UPS-Link SmartUPS Protocol Description', 4, '2010-12-01 12:12:36', '<p><font size=\"7\"><strong><font color=\"#993300\">COMM</font></strong></font></p><p><strong><font size=\"6\">UPS-Link</font></strong></p><p><strong><font size=\"6\">SmartUPS Protocol Description</font></strong></p><p><font size=\"3\"><a href=\"../doc/comm/UPS-Link_SmartUPS.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"COMM - UPS-Link SmartUPS Protocol Description\">COMM - UPS-Link SmartUPS Protocol Description</a></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(31, 'Escape characters sequences replacement', 4, '2011-01-20 14:01:03', '<p><font size=\"4\"><strong><u>Escape characters sequences replacement</u></strong></font></p><p>This generic escape characters sequence are used to replace in the string a specifics characters unwritable</p><p><strong>Examples:</strong></p><blockquote><u>SCPI command to initialize an instrument</u> </blockquote><blockquote>ASRL4::INSTR(*RST<strong></strong>*CLS<font color=\"#ff0000\"></font>SYST:REM<font color=\"#ff0000\"></font>DISP:TEXT &quot;STAMP3 OK&quot;<strong></strong>)&nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote><font size=\"2\">The </font><strong></strong><font color=\"#000000\"> escape </font>characters <font color=\"#000000\">sequence is replaced by the character 10</font>&nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote><font size=\"2\">The </font><strong></strong><font color=\"#000000\"> escape </font>characters <font color=\"#000000\">sequence is replaced by the character 13</font>&nbsp;</blockquote><blockquote>&nbsp;</blockquote><p><strong> </strong><strong><font color=\"#000000\">Escape </font>characters <font color=\"#000000\">sequence </font></strong><strong>list:</strong></p><p><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><font color=\"#000000\"><u>Escape</u></font></td><td><u><br /></u></td><td><u>Function&nbsp;</u></td><td><u><br /></u></td><td><u>Code</u>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&lt;<strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">CR</font></strong>&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>carriage return</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>13&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#800000\">&nbsp;\\r</font></strong>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>carriage return</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>13</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;<strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">LF</font></strong>&gt;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font></td><td>line feed</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>10</td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#800000\">&nbsp;\\n</font></strong>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>line feed</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>10</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;<strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">NL</font></strong>&gt;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>new line</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>13+10</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;<strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">EOL</font></strong>&gt;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>end of line</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>13+10&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;<strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">TAB</font></strong>&gt;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>tabulation&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>07&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;<strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">NULL</font></strong>&gt;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>null char&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>00&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#800000\">&nbsp;\\0</font></strong></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>null char&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>00&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;&lt;<strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">SP</font></strong>&gt;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>space&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>20&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#800000\">&nbsp;\\s</font></strong></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>space&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;<font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td>20</td></tr></tbody></table></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><font color=\"#000000\">Printer escape </font>characters <font color=\"#000000\">sequence </font></strong><strong>list:</strong></p><p><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><font color=\"#000000\"><u>Escape</u></font></td><td><u><br /></u></td><td><u>Code</u>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">&lt;^a&gt;</font></strong> to <strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">&lt;^z&gt;</font></strong>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>01 to 26</td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">&lt;^A&gt;</font></strong> to <strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">&lt;^Z&gt;</font></strong>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font></td><td>01 to 26</td></tr></tbody></table></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong><font color=\"#000000\">Boolean </font>characters <font color=\"#000000\">replacement </font></strong><strong>list:</strong></p><p><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td><font color=\"#000000\"><u>Bool</u></font></td><td><u><br /></u></td><td><u>Char</u></td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">Y</font></strong>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font>&nbsp;</td><td>&quot;1&quot;</td></tr><tr><td><strong><font color=\"#0000ff\">N</font></strong>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&nbsp;&rarr;</font></td><td>&quot;0&quot;</td></tr></tbody></table>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>', '', '', 0, 't'),
(32, 'POWER LEM - NORMA D3000 D4000 D5000', 4, '2011-01-17 09:11:36', '<p><font size=\"7\"><font color=\"#993300\"><strong>POWER METERS</strong></font></font></p><p><font size=\"6\"><strong>NORMA LEM D3000 D4000 D5000</strong></font></p><p><font size=\"6\"><strong>Digital Power Meters&nbsp;</strong></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><font size=\"3\"><a href=\"../doc/instrument/power/N3_4_5000_RC_Manual_214.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"POWER - NORMA LEM  D3-4-5000 &rarr; User Manual\">POWER - NORMA LEM D3-4-5000 &rarr; User Manual</a></font></p>', '', '', 0, 't');
