(33, 'SCPI commands for the JBUS plug-in (Stamp3PlugInJBUS.vi)', 5, '2011-08-09 13:35:11', '<p><strong><u><br /></u></strong></p><p><strong><u>SCPI commands for the JBUS plug-in (Stamp3PlugInJBUS.vi</u></strong>)</p><br /><p>&nbsp;<u><strong>1. Plug-in setting : </strong></u></p><blockquote><p>This section gives all the SCPI commands necessary to the serial port configuration. </p></blockquote><blockquote><p><em><u>1.1. Initialization :</u></em></p><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">COMx:</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">1200,8</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,10</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"174\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"height: 24px; width: 80px\">&nbsp;Explanation : </td><td style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#800000\">COMx</font></td><td style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Serial port </font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">1200</font>&nbsp; <br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Baud rate (bits/s)</font> </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">8</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Data bits</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Parity (0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;odd&quot;, 2 : &quot;even&quot;, 3 : &quot;mark&quot;, 4 : &quot;space&quot;)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">10</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Stop bits </font><font color=\"#808080\">(</font><font color=\"#808080\">10 : &quot;1 bit&quot;,&nbsp; 15 : &quot;1,5 bits&quot;, 20 : &quot;2 bits&quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Flow control (</font><font color=\"#808080\">0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;XON/XOFF&quot;, 2 : &quot;RTS/CTS&quot;, 3 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">RTS/CTS</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;,</font><font color=\"#808080\"> 4 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;, </font><font color=\"#808080\">5 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote><p><em><u>1.2. Change serial port settings :</u></em> </p><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:SET(</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">1200,8</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,0</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"70\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">1200</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Baud rate (bits/s)</font> </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">8</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Data bits</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Parity (0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;odd&quot;, 2 : &quot;even&quot;, 3 : &quot;mark&quot;, 4 : &quot;space&quot;)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">10</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 537px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Stop bits (</font><font color=\"#808080\">10 : &quot;1.0 bits&quot;,&nbsp; </font><font color=\"#808080\">15 : &quot;1.5 bits&quot;, </font><font color=\"#808080\">20 : &quot;2.0 bits&quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> <p><em><u>1.2. Synchronize serial port :</u></em> </p><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:SYNC(<font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font></font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,CR</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">,1</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"70\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">0</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Flow control (</font><font color=\"#808080\">0 : &quot;none&quot;,&nbsp; 1 : &quot;XON/XOFF&quot;, 2 : &quot;RTS/CTS&quot;, 3 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">RTS/CTS</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;,</font><font color=\"#808080\"> 4 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;, </font><font color=\"#808080\">5 : &quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">XON/XOFF&amp;</font><font color=\"#808080\">DTR/DSR</font><font color=\"#808080\">&quot;</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font> </td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">CR</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Termination char </font><font color=\"#808080\">(\'CR\', \'LF\', \'CRLF\'</font><font color=\"#808080\">)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">1</font><br /></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">Timeout (ms)</font></td></tr><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"height: 24px\">&nbsp;</td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">10</font></td><td valign=\"top\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 537px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Rate (ms)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> <p><em><u>1.4. Open serial port :</u></em> </p> </blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:OPEN()</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote><blockquote><em><font color=\"#999999\">Note : The microlink authentication is done at this step, which explains the fact that thi step is relatively long.</font></em></blockquote><p><em><u>1.5. Close serial port :</u></em></p></blockquote>  <blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:PARAM:CLOSE()</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></blockquote><p>&nbsp;<u><strong>2</strong><strong>. Send data :</strong></u></p><blockquote>This section gives all the available SCPI commands to send data to the unit under test via the serial port.&nbsp; <br /></blockquote><blockquote><em><font color=\"#999999\">Note : For each data type (order, parameter, string, file), the &quot;</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#999999\">&quot;  parameter refers to the definition of the data, made in the STAMP  settings (the label being linked to the product address where the data  will be written). </font></em></blockquote><blockquote><em><u>2.1. Order :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote> <blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:SEND:ORDER(<font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">,VALUE</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL</font></font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Order label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">VALUE</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Order value (hexadecimal)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>2.2. Parameter :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:SEND:</font><font color=\"#800000\">PARAM</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,VALUE</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL</font></font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Parameter label<br /></font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">VALUE</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Parameter value (decimal)<br /></font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>2.3. String :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:SEND:STRING</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,STRING</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL</font></font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">String label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">STRING</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">String value (no quotes)<br /></font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>2.4. File :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:SEND:FILE</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,PATH</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">File label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">File path (*)<br /></font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><p><font color=\"#808080\">(*) : See Paragraph 5 for more details</font> </p></blockquote><p><u><strong>3</strong><strong>. Read data :</strong></u></p><blockquote>This section gives all the available SCPI commands to read data from the unit under test via the serial port.&nbsp; </blockquote><blockquote><em><font color=\"#999999\">Note : For each data type (order, parameter, string, file), the &quot;</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#999999\">&quot;  parameter refers to the definition of the data, made in the STAMP  settings (the label being linked to the product address where the data  will be written). </font></em></blockquote><blockquote><em><u>3.1. Status :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote> <blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:STATUS(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">) <font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Status label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"> <font color=\"#008080\">VAR</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Variable in which the status will be stored </font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><em><u>3.2. Value :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:VALUE</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font><font color=\"#800000\"> </font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Value label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"> <font color=\"#008080\">VAR</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Variable in which the value will be stored </font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>3.3. String :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:STRING</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font><font color=\"#800000\"> </font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">String label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"> <font color=\"#008080\">VAR</font></font><br /></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Variable in which the string will be stored </font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>3.4. File :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:FILE</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,PATH1,PATH2</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">File label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH1</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Path of the file that contains the list of the parameters to read</font> <font color=\"#808080\">(*)</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH2</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Path of the file in which the data read will be stored</font><font color=\"#808080\"> (*)</font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><p><font color=\"#808080\">(*) : See Paragraph 5 for more details</font>&nbsp; </p></blockquote><p><strong><u>4. Check data</u></strong></p><blockquote>This section gives all the available SCPI commands to check data content from the unit under test via the serial port.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /></blockquote><blockquote><em><font color=\"#999999\">Note : For each data type (order, parameter, string, file), the &quot;</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#999999\">&quot;  parameter refers to the definition of the data, made in the STAMP  settings (the label being linked to the product address where the data  will be written). </font></em></blockquote><blockquote><em><u>4.1. Status :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote> <blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:WSTATUS(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,STATE,TIME,LOOP</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">) </font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Status label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">STATE</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Expected status (hexadecimal)<br /></font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">TIME</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum time before end of check</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LOOP</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum number of check attempts</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"> <font color=\"#008080\">VAR</font></font><br /></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Variable in which the status will be stored </font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote></blockquote><blockquote><em><u>4.2. Value :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:VALUE</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">,VALUE,TIME,LOOP</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">) </font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Value label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">VALUE</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Expected value</font><font color=\"#808080\"> (decimal)</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">TIME</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum time before end of check</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LOOP</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum number of check attempts</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"> <font color=\"#008080\">VAR<br /></font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Variable in which the value will be stored </font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>4.3. String :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:WSTRING</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">,STRING,TIME,LOOP</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">) </font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#008080\">~(VAR)~</font></font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font> </td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">String label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">STRING</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Expected string value<br /></font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">TIME</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum time before end of check</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LOOP</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Maximum number of check attempts</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#800000\"> <font color=\"#008080\">VAR</font></font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Variable in which the string will be stored </font></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><em><u>4.4. File :</u></em></blockquote><blockquote><blockquote><table border=\"0\"><tbody><tr><td align=\"left\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Command :</td><td><font color=\"#800000\">UUT:COMM:READ:CFILE</font><font color=\"#800000\">(</font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCOL,</font></font><font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL,PATH</font></font><font color=\"#800000\">)</font></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table border=\"0\" width=\"713\" height=\"29\"><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 80px; height: 24px\">Explanation : <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 40px\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PROTOCO</font><font color=\"#0000ff\">L</font></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 20px\"><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> <br /></td><td valign=\"top\" style=\"width: 500px\"><font color=\"#808080\">Protocol short name</font> </td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">LABEL</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">File label</font></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></td><td><font color=\"#808080\">&rarr;</font> </td><td><font color=\"#808080\">Path of the file that contains the list of the parameters to read, and the expected values</font><br /></td></tr></tbody></table></blockquote> </blockquote><p><strong><u>5. File infos</u></strong></p><blockquote><p>&nbsp;With the JBUS plugin, it\'s possible to read, send or check a list of values given in a file (whose path is given in the <font color=\"#800000\"><font color=\"#0000ff\">PATH</font></font> parameter).</p><p>The following example gives an overview of the informations that can be found in this kind of file : </p><p><font color=\"#999999\">[UUT_DESCRIPTION]<br />serial =UUT_SERIAL</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">reference = UUT_REF<br />date = MM/DD/YYYY<br />time = HH:MM:SS</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\">path_template = path/to/the/template.ini</font></p><p><font color=\"#999999\"><br />[PARAMETERS]<br />post_delay = 0.5<br /><br />[STATUS]<br />MODE_NUL = 1</font></p><p>  <font color=\"#999999\"><br />[VALUE]<br />GET_COEFF_K1 = 2.40</font> </p><p> <font color=\"#999999\"><br />[STRING]<br />GET_SERIAL_NUMBER = &quot;SERIAL_NB&quot;</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The first section (<font color=\"#999999\">UUT_DESCRIPTION</font>) gives the global informations relative to the unit under test.</p><p>The second section (<font color=\"#999999\">PARAMETERS</font>) sets the plugin parameter.The &quot;<font color=\"#999999\">post_delay</font>&quot;  parameter sets the wait time (in seconds) when reading or sending  parameters. It must be adapted to the unit under test time response  (default value : 0.5 second). </p><p>The three other sections (<font color=\"#999999\">STATUS</font>,  <font color=\"#999999\">VALUE</font>,  <font color=\"#999999\">STRING</font>) list all the parameters that will be read, sent or check in the unit under test.</p></blockquote>', '', '', -1, 't'),
(34, 'Add SCPI Commands', 22, '2013-08-21 08:26:19', '<p>&nbsp;</p><p style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt\"><strong>Search a string in file (.txt) </strong></p>    <p>DIV:MISC:<strong><span style=\"color: red\">TEXT</span></strong>:<strong><span style=\"color: red\">SEARCH</span></strong> ( <em>s</em><em>trin</em><em>g search</em>, &nbsp;<em>path.txt</em>,  <em>GOTO</em>, <em>loop</em>)</p>    <p style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt\"><strong>Convert Float number to Integer number </strong></p>    <p>DIV:MISC:VAL:<strong><span style=\"color: red\">FLOAT2INT</span> </strong>(<em>value</em>)&nbsp; ~ (<em>value return</em>) ~</p>    <p style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt\"><strong>Round and </strong><span class=\"hps\"><strong><span style=\"color: #222222\">truncates</span></strong></span><span class=\"hps\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; color: #222222\"> </span></span><strong>floating number</strong></p>    <p>DIV:MISC:VAL:<strong><span style=\"color: red\">ROUND  </span></strong>(<em>value,offset</em>) ~ (<em>value return</em>) ~</p>    <p style=\"margin-left: 18.0pt\"><strong>Read serial string text and save (in  .txt) file</strong></p>    <p>UUT:COMM:READ:<strong><span style=\"color: red\">STRINGLONG</span></strong> (<em>protocol</em>,  <em>variable</em>) ~ ( <em>path.txt</em> ) ~</p>    <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">Increase  serial port buffer to 8000 bytes</span></p>    <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">Save  all buffer in txt file</span></p>    <p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Insert a comment line in code</span></strong> &nbsp;</p><p style=\"tab-stops: list 72.0pt\"><span>UUT:DIV:MISC:JUMP:<strong><span style=\"color: red\">COMMENT</span></strong>  (<em>comment</em>)</span></p>    ', '', '', -1, 't');
